import{_ as t,o as e,c as l,R as i}from"./chunks/framework.RpFkmAtX.js";const p=JSON.parse('{"title":"状语从句","description":"","frontmatter":{},"headers":[],"relativePath":"catti/grammer/09状语从句.md","filePath":"catti/grammer/09状语从句.md"}'),o={name:"catti/grammer/09状语从句.md"},s=i('<h1 id="状语从句" tabindex="-1">状语从句 <a class="header-anchor" href="#状语从句" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;状语从句&quot;">​</a></h1><ul><li>状语从句的本质来讲就是用<strong>不同的连词</strong>将几个分句连接起来，以表达分句之间特定的逻辑关系。</li><li><strong>状语从句的省略条件</strong>应同时满足以下两点，此时，可将从句主语和be动词省去 <ul><li>当主句的主语和从句主语一致，<strong>或</strong>从句主语是it</li><li>从句谓语中含有be动词 <ul><li>Metals expand <strong>when heated</strong> and contract <strong>when cooled</strong>.</li><li>The kind of tree grows favorably <strong>where wet</strong>. ≈ where it is wet</li><li><strong>Although not a economist himself</strong>(≈Although he is not a economist himself), Dr. Smith has long been a severe critic of the government&#39;s economic policies.</li></ul></li></ul></li></ul><h2 id="时间状语从句" tabindex="-1">时间状语从句 <a class="header-anchor" href="#时间状语从句" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;时间状语从句&quot;">​</a></h2><h3 id="常见引导词" tabindex="-1">常见引导词 <a class="header-anchor" href="#常见引导词" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;常见引导词&quot;">​</a></h3><h4 id="when" tabindex="-1">when <a class="header-anchor" href="#when" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;when&quot;">​</a></h4><ul><li><p>when充当时间连词时的意思主要包含两个方面</p><ul><li>at the time(在...时刻)，从句谓语动词通常是短暂动词</li><li>during the time，从句谓语动词通常是延续动词</li></ul></li><li><p>常见主从时态搭配</p><ul><li><p>过去的动作</p><ul><li><p>表示从句动作先发生：一般过去时(主)+一般过去时/过去完成时(从)，</p><ul><li>He left when I got there.</li><li>He left when I had got there.</li><li>我到了以后他才离开</li></ul></li><li><p>表示主句动作先发生：过去完成时(主)+一般过去时(从)，</p><ul><li>I had started my dinner when he left.</li></ul></li><li><p><strong>一般过去时与过去进行时的互相搭配</strong></p><ul><li>这种时态搭配下与主句从句没有关系，只与动作的长短的有关系，短暂动作一般用过去时，延续动作用过去进行时 <ul><li><p>一般过去时(主)+过去进行时(从)</p><ul><li>The door rang <strong>when(during the time)</strong> I was telephoning.</li></ul></li><li><p>过去进行时(主)+一般过去时(从)</p><ul><li>I was telephoning <strong>when(at the time</strong>) suddenly the door rang. 此时when强调某个动作突然发生，所以在when引导的从句中可以添加suddenly一词</li></ul></li></ul></li></ul></li></ul></li><li><p>将来的动作</p><ul><li><p>表示从句动作先发生</p><ul><li>一般将来时(主)+一般现在时(从) <ul><li>I&#39;ll tell him about it when he comes back.</li></ul></li><li>一般将来时(主)+现在完成时(从) <ul><li>从句中使用现在完成时是为了强调：在从句动作结束之后，主句动作才开始发生，此时的从句动作一般都是需要持续一段时间的 <ul><li>I&#39;ll go when I <strong>have had</strong> my dinner. 我吃完饭就去</li></ul></li></ul></li></ul></li><li><p>表示主句动作先发生</p><ul><li>将来完成时(主)+一般将来时(从) <ul><li>The performer <strong>will already have played</strong> the music when we <strong>get</strong> there. 一会我们到的时候，那位演奏家一定已经弹完那首曲子了</li></ul></li></ul></li><li><p>将来进行时(主)+从句一般现在时， 类似上述的一般过去时与过去进行时的互相搭配</p><ul><li>The performer <strong>will be playing</strong> the music when we <strong>get</strong> there. 一会我们到的时候，那位演奏家一定正在弹那首曲子</li></ul></li></ul></li><li><p>现在一般的动作，主从句都用一般现在时，常用来阐明一个道理，名言警句中</p><ul><li>When your attitudes <strong>are</strong> right, there <strong>is</strong> no barrier too high, no valley too deep, no dream too extreme, no challenge too great for me.</li><li>常用的固定结构：when it comes to ... 当说到... <ul><li>Doing your homework is a sure way to improve your test scores, and this is especially true <strong>when it comes to</strong> classroom tests.</li></ul></li></ul></li></ul></li><li><p>whenever引导时间状语从句，表示“无论何时”，相当于when的强调形式</p><ul><li>Whenever you say &quot;I&#39;m sorry&quot;, look the person right in the eyes`.</li></ul></li></ul><h4 id="while" tabindex="-1">while <a class="header-anchor" href="#while" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;while&quot;">​</a></h4><ul><li>while充当时间连词是意思相当于during that time(在...期间)，与when的区别主要在于while通常只接延续动词</li><li>while除了表示时间外，还有另外三种意思：表示条件的“只要”，表示对比的“然而”，表示让步的“尽管”</li></ul><h4 id="as" tabindex="-1">as <a class="header-anchor" href="#as" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;as&quot;">​</a></h4><ul><li>as引导时间状语<strong>从句</strong>时，相当于while， <strong>后面要接延续动词</strong>，主句延续动词，短暂动词皆可，一般翻译成**“正当...”，“随着...”，“一边...一边...”**</li></ul><h4 id="before" tabindex="-1">before <a class="header-anchor" href="#before" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;before&quot;">​</a></h4><ul><li>引导时间状语从句类似when存在主从时态搭配，常见的是过去完成时(主)+一般过去时(从) <ul><li>He <strong>had never gambled</strong> <em>before</em> the casino <strong>sent</strong> him a coupon for $20 worth of gambling. // 在...之前</li></ul></li><li>汉译特点 <ul><li>which took root in Europe long <strong>before</strong> people realized how diverse languages could be. // 英文中，before引导的从句一般接肯定形式，但在翻译成汉语时，往往处理成否定的意思 - 这一观点早在人们<strong>尚未认识到语言的千差万别以前</strong>就已在欧洲扎下了根</li><li>“Celebrate!” commanded the ads for the arthritis drug Celebrex, <strong>before</strong> we found out it increase the risk of heart attacks. // 前后对比关系，带有转折意味 - 治疗关节炎的药物Celebrex这个广告鼓动人们去“欢乐”，<strong>结果</strong>我们发现这种药品会加大罹患心脏病的危险‘</li><li>It took a few months of investigation before it became clear. // before引导的从句之前若接有一段时间，此时该从句可以翻译成“<strong>在多长时间之后才...</strong>” - 经过了几个月的调查之后，情况才开始变的明朗</li></ul></li></ul><h4 id="after" tabindex="-1">after <a class="header-anchor" href="#after" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;after&quot;">​</a></h4><ul><li>也存在各种主从时态搭配关系，常见的一种是一般过去时(主)+过去完成时(从) <ul><li>I <strong>moved</strong> to America after I <strong>had learned</strong> English for ten years.</li></ul></li></ul><h4 id="since" tabindex="-1">since <a class="header-anchor" href="#since" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;since&quot;">​</a></h4><ul><li>详见完成时态关于since的阐述 <ul><li>接短暂动词</li><li>接延续动词 <ul><li>一般过去时 - 从句动作“<strong>结束</strong>”以来，主句活动还在持续</li><li>现在完成时 - 从句动作“<strong>开始</strong>”以来，主句活动还在持续</li></ul></li><li>动词延续性或短暂性不限，从句可用完成进行时态have been doing</li></ul></li></ul><h4 id="until" tabindex="-1">until <a class="header-anchor" href="#until" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;until&quot;">​</a></h4><ul><li>本质思维：<strong>一个(主句)动作一直持续到某一个时间点</strong>，具体说就是：until前面的主句或句子的谓语必须是延续性的，而until后面接的从句的谓语必须是短暂性动作或时间点</li><li>句型结构 <ul><li>肯定形式 <ul><li>until作为<strong>连词</strong> - 主句的<strong>延续动词</strong>+until+包含短暂动词的<strong>从句</strong><ul><li>Wait until he comes back.</li></ul></li><li>until作为<strong>介词</strong> - 主句的<strong>延续动词</strong>+until+时间点(<strong>名词短语</strong>) <ul><li>I will be away from my office until next Tuesday.</li></ul></li></ul></li><li>否定形式 - 因为否定之后表示的是一个状态，而状态是延续的，也就是我们常说的<strong>not...until(直到...才)</strong><ul><li>until作为<strong>连词</strong> - not意义+主句的<strong>短暂动词</strong>+until+包含短暂动词的<strong>从句</strong><ul><li>He didn&#39;t leave the office until his boss came back.</li></ul></li><li>until作为<strong>介词</strong> - not意义+主句的<strong>短暂动词</strong>+until+时间点(<strong>名词短语</strong>) <ul><li>I didn&#39;t go to bed until 12 o&#39;clock last night.</li></ul></li><li>not...until常见变体 <ul><li>变体一：until置于句首，只需将until后面的所有成分提到句首 <ul><li><strong>Until</strong> he saw his mother, the little boy <strong>didn&#39;t smile</strong>.</li></ul></li><li>变体二：倒装结构 <ul><li>在变体一基础上将否定词not提到句首</li><li><strong>Not until</strong> he saw his mother, <strong>did</strong> the little boy <strong>smile</strong>.</li></ul></li><li>变体三：强调结构 <ul><li>由结构三与强调结构It was ... that复合而成</li><li><strong>It was not until</strong> he saw his mother <strong>that</strong> the little boy smiled.</li></ul></li></ul></li></ul></li></ul></li></ul><h4 id="一-就-结构" tabindex="-1">&quot;一......就&quot;结构 <a class="header-anchor" href="#一-就-结构" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;&quot;一......就&quot;结构&quot;">​</a></h4><ul><li><strong>从句动作先</strong>于主句动作 <ul><li>常见引导词：<strong>as soon as, once, the minute, the moment, the instant, immediately, directly, instantly</strong> eg. <ul><li>It began to rain <strong>as soon as</strong>(可替换成上面的连词) we began having dinner</li></ul></li><li>以上连词用法和句式结构一样，主从句时态一般一致 <ul><li>表示将来的动作，主句一般将来时，从句一般现在时</li><li>表示过去的动作，主从都一般过去时</li></ul></li></ul></li><li><strong>主句动作先</strong>于从句动作 <ul><li>常见引导词：<strong>hardly...when，scarcely...when, no sooner...than</strong></li><li>以上连词用法和句式结构不一样，主从句时态一般也不一致 <ul><li>一般多用来表示过去动作，主句过去完成时且常倒装，从句一般过去时，可与as soon as等主从互换 <ul><li><strong>No sooner(Hardly/Scarcely)</strong> had I arrived home <strong>than(when)</strong> it began to rain.</li><li>It began to rain as soon as I arrived home.</li></ul></li></ul></li></ul></li></ul><h4 id="by-the-time" tabindex="-1">by the time <a class="header-anchor" href="#by-the-time" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;by the time&quot;">​</a></h4><ul><li>介词短词但起着连词的作用，后面可接一个从句，“在...之前”，强调“一个动作在另外一个动作发生之前已经完成”，主句要用完成时态 <ul><li>We <strong>had</strong> already <strong>left</strong> by the time the they <strong>arrived</strong>. // 表过去动作，</li><li>We <strong>will have</strong> already <strong>left</strong> by the time the they <strong>arrive</strong>. // 表将来动作</li></ul></li></ul><h4 id="表时间的名词短语引导的时间状语从句" tabindex="-1">表时间的名词短语引导的时间状语从句 <a class="header-anchor" href="#表时间的名词短语引导的时间状语从句" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;表时间的名词短语引导的时间状语从句&quot;">​</a></h4><ul><li>类似next time, every time, each time, the day, the week等名词短语也可当做连词来用，引导时间状语从句 <ul><li><strong>Every time</strong> I listen to your advice, I get into trouble.</li><li>the first time <strong>vs</strong> for the first time</li></ul></li></ul><h2 id="地点状语从句" tabindex="-1">地点状语从句 <a class="header-anchor" href="#地点状语从句" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;地点状语从句&quot;">​</a></h2><h3 id="常见引导词-1" tabindex="-1">常见引导词 <a class="header-anchor" href="#常见引导词-1" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;常见引导词&quot;">​</a></h3><ul><li>通常由where引导，“where+陈述句”从句可以放在<strong>句首或句末</strong><ul><li>Stay where you are.</li><li>句首往往在翻译失去地点的含义了，要灵活处理 <ul><li>Where there is a will, there is a way. 有志者事竟成</li></ul></li></ul></li><li>wherever, anywhere, everywhere也可引导地点状语从句 <ul><li>Everywhere they appeared, there were ovations.(热烈欢迎)</li></ul></li></ul><h2 id="原因状语从句" tabindex="-1">原因状语从句 <a class="header-anchor" href="#原因状语从句" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;原因状语从句&quot;">​</a></h2><h3 id="常见引导词-2" tabindex="-1">常见引导词 <a class="header-anchor" href="#常见引导词-2" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;常见引导词&quot;">​</a></h3><ul><li><p>because</p><ul><li><strong>语气最强，只有它才能回答why的问句</strong>，才能被only, just, perhaps等来修饰</li><li>从句显得比主句重要，强调原因</li></ul></li><li><p>since</p><ul><li>常翻译成“既然”，通常放在句首，表示已知的事实，不需要强调</li><li>显得从句次要，主句重要，说明要做什么事</li></ul></li><li><p>as</p><ul><li>与since用法差不多</li><li>主从句位置平等</li></ul></li><li><p>for</p><ul><li>表示推断的理由，是对前面分句内容加以解释或说明</li><li>主从句位置平等</li></ul></li><li><p>表示因果关系的介词</p><ul><li>because of, due to, owing to，后面接名词短语，不接从句</li></ul></li><li><p>其他复合连词表示原因</p><ul><li><p>in that - &quot;原因就在于&quot;，引导的从句放在主句后面，通常是在作比较</p><ul><li>Mercury differs from other industrial metals <strong>in that</strong> it is a liquid.</li></ul></li><li><p>seeing (that), now (that), considering (that), given (that) - &quot;鉴于某个事实，考虑到&quot;</p><ul><li><strong>Now that</strong> you are sixteen, you can get a driver&#39;s license.</li></ul></li><li><p>not that... but that... - 不是因为...而是因为...</p><ul><li>I haven&#39;t finished writing the report yet, <strong>not that</strong> I&#39;m lazy, <strong>but that</strong> I have no time.</li></ul></li><li><p>inasmuch as, insomuch as, in as much as, in so much as - 可表原因，通常只用于书面语或演讲中</p><ul><li>Inasmuch as the two government leaders could not reach an agreement, the possibilities for peace are still remote. // 由于双方政府的领导人无法达成一致，实现和平的可能性依然渺茫</li></ul></li></ul></li><li><p>because的否定转移，在主句是否定的情况下，because引导的从句的翻译可分为以下三种情况：</p><ul><li><p><strong>I don&#39;t study</strong> English just <strong>because</strong> it is so difficult. //只能按正常情况翻译</p><ul><li>我不学英文，因为它太难了</li></ul></li><li><p><strong>I don&#39;t study</strong> English just <strong>because</strong> I like to. // 只能按否定转移来翻译</p><ul><li>我学英文并不是因为我喜欢英文(否定了because引导的从句)</li><li>如果正常来翻就是：我不学英文，就是因为我喜欢英文。明显不符合逻辑</li></ul></li><li><p>两种翻译都可，具体要看上下文</p><ul><li>You <strong>don&#39;t</strong> love a woman <strong>because</strong> she is beautiful.</li><li>你不爱一个女人，因为她太漂亮了</li><li>你不是因为一个女人的美貌而爱他</li></ul></li><li><p>其实，否定转移并不局限与because引导从句，若是在口语中，一般句中重读什么词就否定什么词</p><ul><li>I didn&#39;t come here to <strong>scold</strong> you. // 我来这里不是为了要批评你</li><li>He won&#39;t go to just <strong>any</strong> school. // 他可不愿意随随便便上一个学校就算了，重读any,won&#39;t 是否定any的，not any 不是任何一个，随便一个就可以的</li></ul></li><li><p>否定转移也为我们理解句子意思提供了一个方向，如果按照正常情况理解不通，就不妨考虑从否定转移的角度来翻译</p></li></ul></li></ul><h2 id="目的状语从句" tabindex="-1">目的状语从句 <a class="header-anchor" href="#目的状语从句" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;目的状语从句&quot;">​</a></h2><h3 id="常见引导词-3" tabindex="-1">常见引导词 <a class="header-anchor" href="#常见引导词-3" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;常见引导词&quot;">​</a></h3><ul><li><p>**so that, in order that, that，**另外在目的状语从句中常常含有may/might, can/could等情态动词</p></li><li><p>若想强调目的状语从句，<strong>可将从句置于句首</strong></p><ul><li><strong>In order that(So that)</strong> my roommate <strong>could</strong> study in peace and quiet, I turned off the TV.</li></ul></li><li><p>目的状语从句简化</p><ul><li><p>可用不定式结构来简化，上述三种对应的是：in order to, so as to do和to do</p><ul><li>We climbed high <strong>in order to/so as to</strong> get a better view. // 注意inorder to放在句首句末都可，so as to不能置于句首</li><li><strong>To acquire</strong> knowledge, one must study.</li></ul></li><li><p>具体指出不定式逻辑主语</p><ul><li>I spoke slowly and clearly <strong>in order for</strong> <em>the audience</em> <strong>to</strong> understand me.</li></ul></li></ul></li><li><p>其他表示目的的连词</p><ul><li><p>Take an umbrella with you <strong>lest(以免，以防止)/for fear that(生怕)/in case(万一)</strong> it (<strong>should</strong>) rain. // should常常被省去</p><ul><li>We had a meeting and talked the matter over face to face, for fear that there should be any misunderstanding. // for fear that或lest在某些句子中具有否定意义，≈in order that...not，即in order that there should not be any misunderstanding</li></ul></li><li><p>The teacher raised his voice <strong>on purpose that(/in the hope that/for the purpose that/to the end that)</strong> the students in the back could hear more clearly.</p></li></ul></li></ul><h2 id="结果状语从句" tabindex="-1">结果状语从句 <a class="header-anchor" href="#结果状语从句" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;结果状语从句&quot;">​</a></h2><ul><li>注意，结果状语从句都要放在主语之后</li></ul><h3 id="常见引导词-4" tabindex="-1">常见引导词 <a class="header-anchor" href="#常见引导词-4" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;常见引导词&quot;">​</a></h3><ul><li><p><strong>so+adj./adv./分词+that</strong>，多数结果状语从句由so ... that引导</p><ul><li>The newly described languages were often <strong>so strikingly</strong> different from the well studied languages <strong>that</strong> ...// adv.</li><li>We are <strong>so accustomed</strong> to adopting a mask before others <strong>that</strong> we end by being unable to recognize ourselves. // 分词</li><li>偶尔也用so that来引导结果状语从句，注意与引导目的状语从句的so that区分，两者区别在于： <ul><li>逗号：引导结果状语时，往往会有逗号隔开主句和从句</li><li>情态动词：结果状语中往往没有情态动词 <ul><li>..., the continent may break entirely along some of these fissures**, so that** the hot spot initiates the formation of a new ocean.</li></ul></li></ul></li></ul></li><li><p><strong>such+名词+that</strong></p><ul><li><p>Diplomats and crabs are creatures who move in <strong>such</strong> a way <strong>that</strong> it is impossible to tell whether they are coming or going. // 外交官和螃蟹是行为方式相同的动物，......</p></li><li><p>such that引导结果状语从句时，such≈so+adj.,那这个adj.具体是什么要根据上下文判断，不过有时很难判断such可能含有的形容词意义，就是表示一种“就是如此”的感受</p><ul><li>His anger was <strong>such that(≈so explosive that)</strong> he lost control of himself.</li></ul></li></ul></li><li><p><strong>so vs. such</strong></p><ul><li><p>such后可以直接接名词</p><ul><li><strong>Such a force</strong> would give France a three-to-two advantage over Britain. // such+名词</li><li>Why should a state of <strong>such deep immobilization</strong> ever have evolved? // such+adj.+名词(单复数，不可数皆可)</li><li>The ministers used &quot;splendid&quot;, &quot;magnificent&quot; and <strong>other such expressions</strong> to describe the King&#39;s new clothes. // 限定词(no,other,some,any,one,two,three等)+such+名词，<strong>five hundred such</strong> planes:五百架这样的飞机</li></ul></li><li><p>so后面不可以直接接名词</p><ul><li>The house is <strong>so expensive</strong> that I can&#39;t afford to buy it. // so+adj./adv.</li><li>This is <strong>so expensive a house</strong> that I can&#39;t afford to buy it. // so+adj.+a(n)+单数可数名词</li><li>The neighbors were making <strong>so much noise</strong> last night that I didn&#39;t sleep well. // so可以与表示数量的形容词连用如many,much,few,little，然后再接名词</li></ul></li></ul></li><li><p>结果状语从句简化</p><ul><li>可以用<strong>不定式来简化</strong>，即<strong>so...as to, such... as to, such as to</strong>,注意不要漏掉as <ul><li>He was <strong>such</strong> a fool <strong>as to</strong> believe him.</li><li>He was <strong>so</strong> foolish <strong>as to</strong> believe him. <ul><li>他是如此愚蠢竟然相信他</li></ul></li><li>Her voice was <strong>such as to</strong> make everyone stare.</li></ul></li></ul></li><li><p>为了强调，可以将主句中的so或者such引导的部分置于句首构成倒装结构</p><ul><li><strong>So terrible was</strong> the storm that the roofs were all ripped off.</li></ul></li><li><p><strong>Such a fool was</strong> he that he believed her.</p><ul><li><strong>Such is human nature</strong> that a great many people are often willing to sacrifice higher pay for the privilege of becoming white-collars workers. // 人性就是如此，......</li><li><em>Were the inventions</em> <strong>so</strong> numerous <em>devised to lessen the drudgery of washing clothes</em> <strong>that</strong> the origin of the washing machine is unclear.</li></ul></li><li><p>其他引导结果状语从句的短语连接词</p><ul><li>to the degree(that), to the extent(that), to such a degree(that), to such an extent(that) <ul><li>The bereaved mother was grieved <strong>to the degree that</strong> she couldn&#39;t eat anything for 3 days.</li><li><strong>To such an extent did he go</strong> on with his empty speech that some of us began to doze. // 倒装，他一直不断进行着自己空洞乏味的演讲，以至于我们当中都有人开始打瞌睡了</li></ul></li></ul></li></ul><h2 id="条件状语从句" tabindex="-1">条件状语从句 <a class="header-anchor" href="#条件状语从句" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;条件状语从句&quot;">​</a></h2><h3 id="非真实条件语句" tabindex="-1">非真实条件语句 <a class="header-anchor" href="#非真实条件语句" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;非真实条件语句&quot;">​</a></h3><ul><li>详见虚拟语气章节笔记</li></ul><h3 id="真实条件句" tabindex="-1">真实条件句 <a class="header-anchor" href="#真实条件句" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;真实条件句&quot;">​</a></h3><h4 id="常见引导词-5" tabindex="-1">常见引导词 <a class="header-anchor" href="#常见引导词-5" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;常见引导词&quot;">​</a></h4><ul><li><p>最常见的if(如果)/unless)(如果不，除非)</p><ul><li>If winter comes, can spring be far behind?</li><li><strong>only if 只有，if only 只要</strong></li><li>must/have to do...if...be to do 如果...必须...，那么就不得不 <ul><li>The first two <strong>must</strong> be equal for all who are being compared, if any comparison in terms of intelligence <strong>is to be made</strong>.</li><li>If it doesn&#39;t rain within the next few weeks, the crops <strong>will have to</strong> be watered if they <strong>are to</strong> survive.</li></ul></li></ul></li><li><p>其他表示条件的连词</p><ul><li>suppose (that), supposing (that), providing/provided (that), so long as, as long as,on condition that, eg. <ul><li>Knowledge helps you to reach the destination <strong>provided</strong> you know what the destination is.</li><li>A man is not old <strong>as long as</strong> he is seeking something.</li></ul></li></ul></li><li><p>其他表示条件意味的句型</p><ul><li><p>祈使句/省略句+and=if 从句+主句</p><ul><li>Spare the rod and spoil the child.=if you spare the rod, you&#39;ll spoil the child. // 孩子不打不成器</li></ul></li><li><p>祈使句/省略句+or/or else=unless 从句+主句</p><ul><li>Give it back to me or (else) I&#39;ll tell your parents.=Unless you give it back to me, I&#39;ll tell your parents.</li></ul></li></ul></li></ul><h2 id="让步状语从句" tabindex="-1">让步状语从句 <a class="header-anchor" href="#让步状语从句" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;让步状语从句&quot;">​</a></h2><h3 id="常见引导词-6" tabindex="-1">常见引导词 <a class="header-anchor" href="#常见引导词-6" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;常见引导词&quot;">​</a></h3><ul><li><p><strong>连词接完整的从句/形容词(≈省略句)/分词(≈省略句)</strong> - <strong>though, although, even though, even if, 主句前不可用but，但可用yet/still</strong></p><ul><li>Although he tried hard, (but ×，yet/still √)he failed.</li></ul></li><li><p><strong>介词接名词(短语)/what引导的名词从句/动名词</strong> - **despite, in spite of, for all, notwithstanding, in the event of **</p><ul><li><strong>In spite of his inexperience</strong>, he did a very good job.</li></ul></li><li><p><strong>置于句首的while一般表示“尽管”</strong>，引导让步状语从句</p></li><li><p>no matter wh-(how) &amp; -ever 形式引导让步状语从句，表示&quot;无论&quot;,除了however，一般单独使用，而however后通常接adj./adv.</p><ul><li><p>We decided to do so, <strong>whatever/no matter what</strong> happens.</p></li><li><p><strong>Whoever may</strong> trouble you, I will help you.</p></li><li><p>But <strong>however amazed</strong> our descendants <strong>may be</strong> at how far from Utopia we wre, they will look just like us.</p><ul><li>从句谓语往往会有may或might。加强让步语气，相当于汉语“可能会多么的”, 有时会把may或might省去</li></ul></li><li><p>Try as he will, no man breaks wholly loose from his first love, <strong>no matter who she (might) be</strong>... //</p></li></ul></li><li><p><strong>as引导倒装句表示让步</strong> - <strong>adj./adv./分词/名词(无冠词)/短语+as+主语+谓语动词</strong></p><ul><li>Young as he is, he is knowledgeable.</li><li>Again as he failed in doing this experiment, he didn&#39;t lose his heart.</li><li>Praised as he was, he remained modest.</li><li>Child as he is, he is knowledgeable.</li><li><strong>Lazy a boy</strong> as he is, he is kind to help others. <ul><li>注意粗体语序</li><li>这里 as 可替换成that/though，但比较少用，<strong>不可以替换成although</strong></li></ul></li><li>还可把动词原形置于句首：v. + as + 主语 + 助动词(may, might, will, would, can, could, do, does, did) <ul><li><strong>Fail as I did</strong>, I would never stop trying.</li><li>Lose money as I did, I got a lot of experience. // 若动词是及物动词，其宾语也要随着动词提前 - 尽管我费了不少钱，但是我获得了很多经验</li></ul></li></ul></li><li><p>as/so + adj. + as + 主谓结构，放在句首表让步</p><ul><li><strong>As much as</strong> John hates to do it, he must stay at home and study tonight.</li><li><strong>As amusing and perceptive as</strong> graffiti may sometimes be, it has by no means won universal approval.</li></ul></li><li><p>句首用be的倒装句表让步</p><ul><li><p>表达两种或以上的情况，可改写成由whether引导的让步状语从句</p><ul><li>All substances, <strong>be they</strong> gaseous, liquid or solid, are made up of atoms. // be they gaseous, liquid or solid=<strong>whether</strong> they <strong>may be</strong> gaseous, liquid or solid 不论...还是</li></ul></li><li><p>只表达一种情况，可改写成由however引导的让步状语从句</p><ul><li><strong>Be it</strong> ever so humble, there is no place like home. // Be it ever so humble,...=<strong>However humble</strong> it <strong>may be</strong>,... 不论多么</li></ul></li></ul></li><li><p>nevertheless - 不过，仍然，尽管如此;moreover - 而且，再者，此外; meanwhile - 在此期间，(于此)同时;</p></li></ul><h2 id="比较状语从句" tabindex="-1">比较状语从句 <a class="header-anchor" href="#比较状语从句" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;比较状语从句&quot;">​</a></h2><h3 id="常见引导词-7" tabindex="-1">常见引导词 <a class="header-anchor" href="#常见引导词-7" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;常见引导词&quot;">​</a></h3><h4 id="as-as" tabindex="-1">as ... as <a class="header-anchor" href="#as-as" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;as ... as&quot;">​</a></h4><h5 id="基本用法" tabindex="-1">基本用法 <a class="header-anchor" href="#基本用法" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;基本用法&quot;">​</a></h5><ul><li>as+adj./adv.+as</li><li>as+adj.+a(n)+可数名词单数+as <ul><li>前一个as作为副词修饰形容词，形容词修饰名词，<strong>注意这里形容词置于不定冠词之前</strong>的特点</li><li>Rarely has a technological development had <strong>as great an impact</strong> on so many aspects of social, economic, and cultural development <strong>as</strong> the growth of electronics. <ul><li>正常语序 A technological development has rarely had as great an impact on ... as the growth of electronics.</li><li>很少有哪项科技的发展能像电子技术的发展这样，对我们的社会，经济以及文化等诸多方面产生如此重要的影响</li></ul></li></ul></li><li>在否定句中第一个as可用so代替 <ul><li>This room is not so large as the one we saw yesterday.</li></ul></li><li>保持句子平衡，从句倒装 <ul><li>as...as+助动词+主语</li><li>Small as it is, the ant is <strong>as</strong> much a creature <strong>as are</strong> all other animals on the earth. <ul><li>as much ... as 在同等程度上，翻译成 和...一样</li></ul></li></ul></li></ul><h5 id="相关句型" tabindex="-1">相关句型 <a class="header-anchor" href="#相关句型" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;相关句型&quot;">​</a></h5><ul><li>as much as结构，不能简单理解成“和...一样多”，它往往是表示两个事物之间程度的比较，表示“在同等程度上”，翻译时要灵活处理 <ul><li>The atmosphere is <strong>as much</strong> a part of the earth <strong>as</strong> are its soils and the waterof its lakes, rivers and oceans. // 地球周围的大气层，<strong>就如同</strong>地球上的泥土及湖泊、河流、海洋中的水<strong>一样</strong>，都是地球的组成部分。</li></ul></li><li>not so much ... as结构用法特点 <ul><li>常见结构：not A so much as B, not so much A as B</li><li>基本含义：与其说A倒不如说B；是B，而不是A</li><li>A和B是两个被比较的平行结构，如：同为介词短语、动词不定式、名词短语或其他平行结构 <ul><li>The great use of a school education is <strong>not so much</strong> to teach you things <strong>as</strong> to teach you the art of learning.</li><li>The trumpet player was certainly loud, but I was <strong>not</strong> bothered by his loudness <strong>so much as</strong> by his lack of talent.</li></ul></li></ul></li><li>(just) as ..., so结构，表示类比，基本意思：“正如......”, 第二句可用倒装结构 <ul><li><strong>Just as</strong> virtue is its own reward, <strong>so</strong> is vice its own punishment. //善有善报，恶有恶报</li><li><strong>As</strong> you sow, <strong>so</strong> you will reap/<strong>so</strong> will you reap. // just可省略，种瓜得瓜，种豆得豆</li></ul></li></ul><h4 id="than" tabindex="-1">than <a class="header-anchor" href="#than" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;than&quot;">​</a></h4><h5 id="基本用法-1" tabindex="-1">基本用法 <a class="header-anchor" href="#基本用法-1" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;基本用法&quot;">​</a></h5><ul><li><p>可比性 - 两个<strong>同类事物</strong>才能比较</p><ul><li>In China the South generally receives much less snow than <strong>does</strong> the North. // 注意这里比较的对象是the South和the North， does the North = the North receives</li></ul></li><li><p>在有than的比较句子中，<strong>主句必须有比较级形式出现</strong></p></li><li><p>保持句子平衡，从句倒装</p><ul><li>than+助动词+主语</li><li>In addition, far more Japanese workers expressed dissatisfaction with their jobs than did their counterparts(职务相当的人) in the 10 other countries surveyed. <ul><li>另外，据调查，不满意自己工作的日本员工比另外10个国家的员工人数要多得多</li></ul></li></ul></li></ul><h5 id="相关句型-1" tabindex="-1">相关句型 <a class="header-anchor" href="#相关句型-1" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;相关句型&quot;">​</a></h5><ul><li>no more ... than结构 <ul><li>基本意思：“同...一样不”，翻译时要表达出<strong>类比关系</strong>：先译主句 - “...不能...,就如同(than引导的从句)...不能”； 先译从句 - “正如(than从句)...不能...，所以...同样不能...”</li><li>有个结构变体：not...any more than</li><li>注意than后的句子为肯定形式，但要翻译成否定含义 <ul><li>The heart is <strong>no more</strong> intelligent <strong>than</strong> the stomach, for they are both controlled by the brain.</li><li>But his primary task is <strong>not</strong> to think about the moral code, which governs his activity, <strong>any more than</strong> a businessman is expected to dedicate his energies to an exploration of rule of conduct in business.</li></ul></li></ul></li></ul><h4 id="倍数比较" tabindex="-1">倍数比较 <a class="header-anchor" href="#倍数比较" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;倍数比较&quot;">​</a></h4><ul><li>常见三种句型(以三倍three times为例) <ul><li>&quot;倍数+比较级&quot; - A is three times bigger(或其他形容词比较级) than B.</li><li>&quot;倍数+as...as&quot; - A is three times as big(或其他形容词原级) as B.</li><li>&quot;倍数+名词&quot; - A is three times the size(或其他形容词对应的名词形式) of B.</li></ul></li></ul><h4 id="the-more-the-more" tabindex="-1">the more..., the more <a class="header-anchor" href="#the-more-the-more" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;the more..., the more&quot;">​</a></h4><ul><li>用法要点 <ul><li>“the+比较级(<strong>从句</strong>)，the+比较级(<strong>主句</strong>)”结构，类似其他从句的“主句用将来时，从句用一般现在时”</li><li><strong>比较级部分都必须要在各自引导的分句中充当一定成分</strong></li><li>翻译时先译从句，再译主句</li></ul></li><li>比较翻译：你用词越准确，人们就越容易理解你的意思 <ul><li><strong>The more exact</strong> you use your words, <strong>the easier</strong> people will understand you. ×</li><li><strong>The more exactly</strong> you use your words, <strong>the more easily</strong> people will understand you.√</li><li><strong>The more exact</strong> words you use, <strong>the easier it is for</strong> people to understand you.√</li><li><strong>The more exact</strong> your words are, <strong>the more easily</strong> people will understand you.√</li></ul></li><li>有个不太常用的变体结构, 意思是一致的 <ul><li><strong>The older</strong> she is, <strong>the more interested</strong> he is in her.</li><li>He is <strong>more interested</strong> in her, <strong>the older</strong> she is.</li></ul></li></ul><h4 id="a-is-to-b-what-as-c-is-to-d结构" tabindex="-1">A is to B what/as C is to D结构 <a class="header-anchor" href="#a-is-to-b-what-as-c-is-to-d结构" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;A is to B what/as C is to D结构&quot;">​</a></h4><ul><li>A与B之间的关系就类似于C和D之间的关系，变体结构：what/as C is to D，so is A to B或A is to B <ul><li>The people is to the people&#39;s army <strong>what(as)</strong> water is to fish. // 军民鱼水情</li><li>As(What) water is to fish, so is the people to the people&#39;s army(people is to the people&#39;s army).</li></ul></li></ul><h4 id="其他" tabindex="-1">其他 <a class="header-anchor" href="#其他" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;其他&quot;">​</a></h4><ul><li>She is more of a musician than her brother. // 她比她哥哥更像一个音乐家</li></ul><h2 id="方式状语从句" tabindex="-1">方式状语从句 <a class="header-anchor" href="#方式状语从句" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;方式状语从句&quot;">​</a></h2><h3 id="常见引导词-8" tabindex="-1">常见引导词 <a class="header-anchor" href="#常见引导词-8" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;常见引导词&quot;">​</a></h3><ul><li><strong>as, like, as if, as though, the way</strong>等，表示动作的方式 <ul><li>When in Rome, do as the Romans do. //入乡随俗</li><li>Do it the way you were taught.</li><li>He looks as if/as though he is an actor.</li><li>Sing like nobody&#39;s listening.</li></ul></li><li>重点<strong>as引导的方式状语从句</strong><ul><li><p>..., look at an organic being <strong>as a savage looks at a ship</strong>, as at something whoolly beyond his comprehension. // 修饰句子的谓语部分</p></li><li><p>Some Asian nations and regions reiterated their opposition to a war, <strong>as did many</strong> of their citizens who worry Bush has already given up on hopes for a peaceful resolution to the crisis. // 倒装结构</p><ul><li>一些亚洲国家和地区重申了他们反对战争的立场，他们的许多公民也持同样的立场，因为他们担心小布什已经放弃了和平解决这一危机的希望。</li></ul></li><li><p>用于否定结构的特殊用法</p><ul><li><p>as前面句子是否定的，as所在的句子本身是肯定的，通常会翻译成“<strong>不像</strong>”</p><ul><li>He <strong>is not arguing</strong>, <strong>as many do</strong>, that we can no longer think straight because we do not talk proper. // 他并没有像许多人那样，认为因为我们话说得不好，就不会正确地思维了</li></ul></li><li><p>as前面句子是肯定的，as所在的句子本身是否定的，通常会翻译成“<strong>但，然而</strong>”</p><ul><li>He could love the child <strong>as</strong> he <strong>did not</strong> love Charles.</li></ul></li></ul></li></ul></li></ul>',69),a=[s];function r(n,h,u,g,d,c){return e(),l("div",null,a)}const b=t(o,[["render",r]]);export{p as __pageData,b as default};
